{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71430e94-9846-4241-bc98-acb5b3f2f2aa","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look for **Apple crash reports** in:\n\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\n\nFiles are named like `YourApp_<date>_<machine>.ips` (or `.crash` on older macOS). They contain the signal, faulting thread, stack traces, and loaded images.\n\nYou can also:\n\n- **Open Console.app** → sidebar → *Crash Reports* to browse them with a GUI.\n- Run `log show --predicate 'eventMessage contains \"YourApp\"' --last 1h` to search system logs.\n- If you need a **core dump** for lldb, enable them first:\n  ```bash\n  ulimit -c unlimited\n  ```\n  Then reproduce the crash — the core file typically lands in `/cores/core.<pid>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4513ea73-2a40-4d54-b001-f5e8044a33d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":257},"id":"51e5eb3a-2508-464d-9a36-f872f8ce2e11","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:02:07.573Z","parentId":"429a0c6f-e52b-4dcf-89bc-fa95fff46a45"}
